name: jdc_person_id
title: JCOIN data commons person identifier
description: The generated unique identifier specific to the JCOIN Data Commons for a given individual (client or staff).

name: hub_id
title: Hub identifier
description: Randomly generated integer for each unique hub.

name: quarter_enrolled
title: Quarter Enrolled
description: The financial quarter and year of enrollment

name: staff_type
title: Staff Type
description: The type of staff (Court Coordinator, Judge, Law Enforcement, Lawyer, Peer, Treatment)

name: current_study_status
title: Current Study Status
description: A summary of the current status of staff member's involvement in study
constraints.enum: On study|Dropped out|Withdrawn by investigator|Completed study|Unknown

name: age
title: Age
description: About how old are you? (top coded at 90)

name: sex_at_birth
title: Sex at birth
description: What sex was originally listed on your birth certificate?

name: gender_id
title: Gender Identity
description: What is your gender identity?
constraints.enum: Male|Female|Transgender man/trans man/female-to-male (FTM)|Transgender woman/trans woman/male-to-female (MTF)|Genderqueer/gender nonconforming/neither exclusively male nor female|Additional gender category (or other)|Not reported
custom.jcoin:notes:
For gender/orientation/identity, use items O1-O2 if possible, otherwise use D4a-D4c.   [Must use one or the other.] 
 False if not 'Male' and not 'Transgender' else True

name: gender_id_condensed
title: Gender Identity (condensed)
description: What is your gender identity?
custom.jcoin:notes: For gender/orientation/identity, use items O1-O2 if possible, otherwise use D4a-D4c.   [Must use one or the other.]

name: race
title: Race
description:
Racial category derived from the individual racial category fields.
  - Exactly one racial category field selected = title of racial category
  - Two or more selected = Multiracial
constraints.enum: White|Black or African American|American Indian or Alaska Native|Asian|Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander|Some other race|Multiracial

name: hispanic_latino
title: Hispanic, Latino, or Spanish Origin
description: Are you of Hispanic, Latino, or Spanish origin?

name: sex_orient_category
title: Sexual orientation

constraints.enum: Straight or heterosexual|Lesbian or gay|Bisexual|Queer,pansexual, and/or questioning|Something else

name: sex_orient_other
title: Sexual orientation:  Other specified
description: Sexual orientation:  Do you think of yourself as

name: ever_pregnant
title: Ever pregnant
description: Have you ever been pregnant?
constraints.enum: Never been pregnant|Currently pregnant|Previously pregnant, had a child|Previously pregnant, did not have a child|Not applicable|Don't know
custom.jcoin:notes: Does this just apply to that past 90 days?  If not, then the participant should be able to check more than one response.

name: marital_status
title: Marital status
description: What is your marital status?

name: living_as_married
title: Married with partner
description: Are you currently living as married with a romantic partner?
constraints.enum: Yes, I am living as married with partner|No, I am not living as married with partner

name: educ_category
title: Education
description: What is the highest grade or level of school you have completed or the highest degree you have received?
constraints.enum: Did not complete high school|GED or equivalent|Regular high school diploma|Some college credit but less than 1 year of college credit|1 or more years of college credit but no degree|Associate's degree (e.g., AA or AS)|Bachelor's degree (e.g.,  BA or BS)|Graduate degree (e.g., MSW, MA, MS, JD, MD, DSW, EdD, PhD)|Other (specify)

name: educ_highest_grade
title: Education:  Highest grade level (if less than GED or h.s. diploma)
description: What is the highest grade completed?

name: educ_other_specified
title: Education: Other specified
description: What is the highest grade or level of school you have completed or the highest degree you have received?

name: visit_number
title: Visit Number
description: A number that identifies the visit (survey administration event) or timepoint of data collection (baseline=1 and each subsequent follow up is 2 or greater).

name: shifted_visit_dt
title: Visit Date (shifted)
description:
This is the date of the visit (ie time point of survey administration)
after shifting by a random number 182 days before or 182 days after the actual
visit date. The shifting is done on the individual level which retains the time
interval between visits (and allows calculations of days between time points
or other date fields which are shifted by the same number of days). To avoid
issues with type conversion errors, the date is of type integer

NOTE: if `days_on_study` is filled out, `shifted_visit_date` is not required.

name: visit_type
title: Visit Type
description: The visit type/category of the survey administration (either baseline or follow up)

name: org_readiness_confidence
title: Confidence to implement
description: Rate each of the following statements on a 5-point scale where 1=Disagree and 5=Agree [People who work here feel confident that the organization can get people invested in implementing [intervention].]]
custom.jcoin:source:
Shea et al., 2014  - Organizational Readiness for Implementing Change: A psychometric assessment of a 
new measure.  Implementation Science 9:7. https://doi.org/10.1186/1748-5908-9-7
